🌱 The root-family idea (clean model)

Core pattern:

Root = invariant meaning core
Affixes = transformations of that core

So a “word family” is basically:

* one root
* many transformations
* shared semantic DNA

⸻

🧩 Example: “struct” (to build)

* structure → the built thing
* construct → build together
* destruct → un-build / take apart
* instruct → build knowledge into someone
* obstruct → block the building / path

The root “struct” = build never disappears.
Each prefix bends it in a direction.

⸻

🔧 Affixes as operators

Think of common prefixes like functions:

* re- → again (rebuild)
* de- → remove / reverse (deconstruct)
* con- → together (construct)
* sub- → under (substructure)

So:

word = operator(prefix) + invariant(root)

That’s very close to how you’ve been thinking in systems terms.

